analysis.description:
MUSystem.transferFee (/unique_contracts/0xcf5dfe6e2fa63af41e9c01df75e79d3fda69b5f3.sol#340-346) sends eth to arbitrary user
	Dangerous calls:
	- creatorOwner.transfer(CurrentPackFee) (/unique_contracts/0xcf5dfe6e2fa63af41e9c01df75e79d3fda69b5f3.sol#344-345)

MUSystem.deposit (/unique_contracts/0xcf5dfe6e2fa63af41e9c01df75e79d3fda69b5f3.sol#346-458) uses a dangerous strict equality:
	- usersWhoBuy[userAddr].UserBuyTokenPackNum == CurrentPackNumber
	- usersWhoBuy[userAddr].UserBuyTokenPackNum == CurrentPackNumber
	- usersWhoSell[userAddr].UserSellTokenPackNum == CurrentPackNumber

MUSystem.BigAmt should be constant (/unique_contracts/0xcf5dfe6e2fa63af41e9c01df75e79d3fda69b5f3.sol#93-94)
MUSystem.CoMargin should be constant (/unique_contracts/0xcf5dfe6e2fa63af41e9c01df75e79d3fda69b5f3.sol#86)
MUSystem.CoOverlap should be constant (/unique_contracts/0xcf5dfe6e2fa63af41e9c01df75e79d3fda69b5f3.sol#87-88)
MUSystem.Disparity should be constant (/unique_contracts/0xcf5dfe6e2fa63af41e9c01df75e79d3fda69b5f3.sol#88-89)
MUSystem.FirstPackTokenPriceSellout should be constant (/unique_contracts/0xcf5dfe6e2fa63af41e9c01df75e79d3fda69b5f3.sol#92-93)
